00:14:44.244 --> 00:14:46.414
can invest in building and scaling

00:14:46.414 --> 00:14:49.074
their technologies now, rather

00:14:49.074 --> 00:14:50.614
than waiting for other customers to

00:14:50.614 --> 00:14:52.964
arrive, which might never happen.

00:14:54.514 --> 00:14:56.524
And they are backing some pretty

00:14:56.524 --> 00:14:59.004
cool projects, so I wanted to tell

00:14:59.014 --> 00:15:01.114
you about a few of them that your

00:15:01.114 --> 00:15:03.264
support has helped make possible.

00:15:04.484 --> 00:15:07.234
Firstly, there’s one called Eion,

00:15:07.544 --> 00:15:09.364
which is a company that works

00:15:09.364 --> 00:15:11.834
with farmers to mix a specially

00:15:11.834 --> 00:15:14.434
developed silicate rock into soil.

00:15:15.604 --> 00:15:18.134
This rock reacts with carbon

00:15:18.134 --> 00:15:21.004
dioxide in the air and eventually

00:15:21.254 --> 00:15:23.004
turns it into a stable form of

00:15:23.004 --> 00:15:25.154
carbon that ends up in the ocean.

00:15:26.074 --> 00:15:28.834
It’s a natural process, but Eion is

00:15:28.844 --> 00:15:31.694
speeding it up, and they’re also helping

00:15:31.694 --> 00:15:34.044
improve soil quality at the same time.

00:15:35.024 --> 00:15:38.104
Another one is called Phlair, which uses

00:15:38.104 --> 00:15:41.814
a process called electrochemical pH-swing.

00:15:42.614 --> 00:15:45.224
It might sound technical, but essentially,

00:15:45.514 --> 00:15:48.173
it captures carbon dioxide from the air

00:15:48.564 --> 00:15:51.694
using a chemical solvent, then permanently

00:15:51.904 --> 00:15:54.214
stores the carbon in construction

00:15:54.214 --> 00:15:56.984
materials, like bricks or concrete,

00:15:57.374 --> 00:15:59.954
so it never returns to the atmosphere.

00:16:00.914 --> 00:16:02.494
Then there’s one with the

00:16:02.594 --> 00:16:05.254
ominous name of Vaulted Deep.

00:16:05.834 --> 00:16:08.434
Maybe it sounds like a horror film, or

00:16:08.554 --> 00:16:11.694
someone’s gaming name, but it's a company

00:16:11.694 --> 00:16:14.554
that basically buries food underground.

00:16:15.334 --> 00:16:16.654
Obviously, it’s a little

00:16:16.654 --> 00:16:18.104
more complicated than this.

00:16:18.394 --> 00:16:20.414
It takes organic waste, things

00:16:20.414 --> 00:16:23.084
like food scraps and agricultural

00:16:23.094 --> 00:16:25.834
leftovers, and injects it deep

00:16:25.874 --> 00:16:28.504
underground in specially built wells.

00:16:29.314 --> 00:16:31.234
As it decomposes, the

00:16:31.254 --> 00:16:33.454
carbon stays locked away.

00:16:34.104 --> 00:16:36.824
Not only does this stop carbon from

00:16:36.844 --> 00:16:39.744
entering the atmosphere, but it solves

00:16:39.744 --> 00:16:43.004
the problem of environmental waste, and it

00:16:43.004 --> 00:16:45.614
doesn’t require fancy new infrastructure.

00:16:46.524 --> 00:16:48.574
And finally, there’s a project

00:16:48.754 --> 00:16:51.034
close to home, at least where I am.

00:16:51.674 --> 00:16:54.474
There’s a Swedish company called Exergi,

00:16:54.814 --> 00:16:57.184
and it’s another nice example of how

00:16:57.184 --> 00:17:00.024
this technology sometimes seems obvious.

00:17:01.384 --> 00:17:04.384
What it is doing is retrofitting a

00:17:04.424 --> 00:17:06.494
biomass power plant in Stockholm.

00:17:07.484 --> 00:17:10.694
This biomass power plant already takes

00:17:10.734 --> 00:17:13.344
waste products from the timber industry,

00:17:13.624 --> 00:17:16.354
such as sawdust, branches, and wood,

00:17:16.654 --> 00:17:19.604
then burns them to generate electricity

00:17:19.674 --> 00:17:20.987
for people living in Stockholm.

00:17:21.394 --> 00:17:24.714
But what this company is doing is

00:17:24.784 --> 00:17:27.364
adapting the power plant so that the

00:17:27.364 --> 00:17:30.764
CO2 generated during this process is

00:17:30.834 --> 00:17:33.234
captured before it’s released into

00:17:33.234 --> 00:17:36.184
the atmosphere, then transporting it

00:17:36.214 --> 00:17:38.904
away and burying it deep underground.

00:17:39.954 --> 00:17:42.494
It’s a nice example because it is a

00:17:42.504 --> 00:17:44.934
mixture between carbon removal and

00:17:45.074 --> 00:17:48.194
emission reduction, and also shows

00:17:48.204 --> 00:17:50.314
how these technologies aren’t always

00:17:50.314 --> 00:17:52.454
rocket science; they just need enough

00:17:52.464 --> 00:17:54.724
people to believe in them so they can be

00:17:54.724 --> 00:17:57.844
scaled and deployed on a global basis.

00:17:58.984 --> 00:18:01.774
And these are just a few of the dozens

00:18:01.774 --> 00:18:04.074
of companies working on this challenge.

00:18:04.454 --> 00:18:06.894
I’ll put a link in the description to

00:18:06.894 --> 00:18:09.474
the Stripe Climate website, so you can

00:18:09.474 --> 00:18:11.214
go and check out some of these companies

00:18:11.314 --> 00:18:13.424
if you are interested; there are some

00:18:13.424 --> 00:18:15.691
really cool ideas and projects in there.

00:18:16.354 --> 00:18:19.074
Some will fail, some will succeed,

00:18:19.504 --> 00:18:21.364
and there’s a real challenge

00:18:21.374 --> 00:18:24.414
in verifying and monitoring how

00:18:24.414 --> 00:18:26.444
much carbon is truly removed.

00:18:27.094 --> 00:18:29.974
But all of them are helping build

00:18:29.980 --> 00:18:32.662
the foundations for what might one

00:18:32.662 --> 00:18:35.172
day be a massive global industry.

00:18:36.122 --> 00:18:39.666
So, can carbon removal save the planet?

00:18:40.302 --> 00:18:42.302
No, not by itself.

00:18:42.902 --> 00:18:45.462
But alongside reducing emissions,

00:18:45.732 --> 00:18:48.232
switching to clean energy, protecting

00:18:48.232 --> 00:18:50.892
forests, and changing how we live

00:18:50.892 --> 00:18:52.881
and work, it’s one of the tools

00:18:52.891 --> 00:18:55.071
we’ll need to have a fighting chance.

00:18:55.803 --> 00:18:58.787
And thanks to you, one of the relatively

00:18:58.787 --> 00:19:01.407
few people on this planet who has helped

00:19:01.407 --> 00:19:04.387
fund real carbon removal, that future

00:19:04.586 --> 00:19:07.577
perhaps looks just a tiny bit brighter.

00:19:08.827 --> 00:19:11.087
OK then, that is it for carbon

00:19:11.087 --> 00:19:12.897
removal, this fascinating and

00:19:12.907 --> 00:19:14.587
vastly important technology.

